cards.rules_text:
Suspend 2 — {0}{U}{U}
Impact — When you cast this spell, you may choose target creature you control; if so, until end of turn all other creatures phase out and the chosen creature gains flying, double strike, and "Whenever this creature deals combat damage to a player, draw two cards."
At the beginning of your end step, exile the chosen creature unless it dealt combat damage to a player.

Flying, ward {2}
Curse of Deception — Whenever a player casts a spell targeting only one creature or player, roll a d6. On a 1 or 2, the creature that player controls with the highest power loses all abilities and becomes a 1/1 green Frog until end of turn. If tied for highest power, that player chooses one.
Whenever a creature becomes a Frog this way, you draw a card.
